4. The Replacement Claim Changes Everything

There is a critical difference between a tool and a replacement.

A calculator did not replace mathematicians; it replaced arithmetic labour.
A spreadsheet did not replace accountants; it replaced manual bookkeeping.
CAD software did not replace engineers; it replaced drafting boards.

These tools increased productivity. They did not replace the professional judgement of the person using them.

But when executives say AI will replace lawyers, consultants, engineers, analysts, and researchers, they are no longer describing a tool. They are describing a substitute decision-maker.

That is a completely different category of product.

And substitute decision-makers carry liability.

If a tool helps a human make a decision, the human is responsible.
If a system is marketed as capable of making the decision, responsibility shifts.

That shift is where the legal exposure lives.

