5. You Cannot Have AGI Marketing and Autocomplete Liability

The AI industry currently operates in a contradiction.

On stage, the language is:
	•	AGI is near
	•	Intelligence is a commodity
	•	AI is superhuman at many intellectual tasks
	•	AI will replace knowledge workers
	•	AI will perform most computer-based intellectual work

But when failures are discussed, the language changes to:
	•	It’s just a tool
	•	It can make mistakes
	•	Humans must verify outputs
	•	It’s an assistant, not a decision-maker
	•	It’s autocomplete

These two positions are not compatible.

You cannot market a system as a mind and defend it in court as a text generator.

You cannot claim replacement-level capability and then claim tool-level responsibility.

At some point, the description used to sell the system and the description used to defend the system must match.

