8. The Inevitable Collision

The trajectory is clear:
	•	Companies are incentivised to make large claims.
	•	Investors reward large claims.
	•	Media amplifies large claims.
	•	Employers act on large claims.
	•	Workers change careers based on large claims.
	•	Governments plan based on large claims.

At some point, the systems will be used in ways that match the claims.
At some point, failures will cause real financial, professional, or legal harm.
At that point, the question will not be philosophical anymore.

The question will be:

Were the capabilities of this system described accurately relative to the way it was foreseeably used?

That is not a technology question.
That is a liability question.

