9. Conclusion — The Record Is Being Written Now

The most important thing happening right now is not just the development of AI systems. It is the creation of a public record.

Every interview, every keynote, every tweet, every claim about AGI, replacement of jobs, superhuman reasoning, and rentable intelligence is part of that record.

If the technology eventually matches those claims, the companies will be remembered as visionaries.

If the technology does not match those claims on the timelines and reliability levels implied, those same statements will be read again in a different context — not as predictions, but as representations.

And representations are what courts, regulators, and historians read when they try to determine whether the public was misled about what a powerful technology could actually do.

The AI industry believes it is currently writing the future.

It may, in fact, be writing the evidence.
